-- Egypt May Get $500 Million Sugar Factory Using Beets, Mena Says
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2013-01-22T12:09:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-22/egypt-may-get-500-million-sugar-factory-using-beets-mena-says.html
Egypt may get a $500 million factory
to produce white sugar from beets in the country, the state-run
Middle East  News Agency  reported, citing Industry Minister Hatem Saleh.  The factory would have a production capacity of 400,000
metric tons, according to the Cairo-based agency, also known as
Mena. The company planning the factory was only identified in
the report as being from the United Arab Emirates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  